The paper is about object detection using deep learning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper discusses various learning strategies and architectures for deep learning, which suggests that it could also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subcategories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (cs.NE) and benchmarks for object detection (cs.MM).
